{"id": "ChIJS2MqK7PDwoARpKQd51brNu0", "rating": 4.6, "userRatingCount": 120, "displayName": {"text": "danbi coffee", "languageCode": "en"}, "reviews": [{"name": "places/ChIJS2MqK7PDwoARpKQd51brNu0/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25ReGVETTFWamRDZHpWeWVsTkdObTFOTkV4VVJrRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "If you’re in Pasadena, this café is absolutely worth a stop. The coffee had an incredible aroma and tasted genuinely exceptional. The tomato basil pastry was savory, flaky, and full of flavor, and the small mango and strawberry cake I had afterward was surprisingly amazing. Everything felt fresh and carefully made — not just the coffee, but the pastries and desserts too. A perfect spot if you appreciate quality flavors and a cozy café experience.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "If you’re in Pasadena, this café is absolutely worth a stop. The coffee had an incredible aroma and tasted genuinely exceptional. The tomato basil pastry was savory, flaky, and full of flavor, and the small mango and strawberry cake I had afterward was surprisingly amazing. Everything felt fresh and carefully made — not just the coffee, but the pastries and desserts too. A perfect spot if you appreciate quality flavors and a cozy café experience.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Young Chung", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110965493684345950702/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW5kgGqbs2yXyo3GdQ14FruvfT7drU7GOkm-bp6Hn_EnyXhaINpUg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2026-05-28T19:21:54.023873665Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25ReGVETTFWamRDZHpWeWVsTkdObTFOTkV4VVJrRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25ReGVETTFWamRDZHpWeWVsTkdObTFOTkV4VVJrRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c3b32b2a634b:0xed36eb56e71da4a4"}, {"name": "places/ChIJS2MqK7PDwoARpKQd51brNu0/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2paNVYwUTBMWEIxTmxCdllsbERSM0JUU1ZKVlQxRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "I love this new Korean cafe in Pasadena. Their matcha is soo good and creamy! The pastries are delicious as well! They have a lot of options to choose from coffee,non caffeinated drinks , tea, pastries. And fruits desserts I’m definitely going to try their cute fruit desserts when I come back.\n\nService is amazing, my drinks and pastries came out really fast and everyone was friendly.\n\nAmbiance is cute, and plenty of seating. They also sell some merch like shirts, coffee, tea and cups.\n\nI got some of their coffee, cups and shirts.\n\nI will definitely comeback.\n\nWhat I got:\nMatcha Rain\nPistachio Croissant\nOrange Grapefruit Black Tea\nTomato Basil Pesto Danish", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "I love this new Korean cafe in Pasadena. Their matcha is soo good and creamy! The pastries are delicious as well! They have a lot of options to choose from coffee,non caffeinated drinks , tea, pastries. And fruits desserts I’m definitely going to try their cute fruit desserts when I come back.\n\nService is amazing, my drinks and pastries came out really fast and everyone was friendly.\n\nAmbiance is cute, and plenty of seating. They also sell some merch like shirts, coffee, tea and cups.\n\nI got some of their coffee, cups and shirts.\n\nI will definitely comeback.\n\nWhat I got:\nMatcha Rain\nPistachio Croissant\nOrange Grapefruit Black Tea\nTomato Basil Pesto Danish", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Katrin Mendoza", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111240994049911798244/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFOCibb__pWle_hT_wGCrZ6NVygKSuuLXjSvcwBTFO2gafAgOF=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2026-04-05T06:36:13.709815832Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2paNVYwUTBMWEIxTmxCdllsbERSM0JUU1ZKVlQxRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2paNVYwUTBMWEIxTmxCdllsbERSM0JUU1ZKVlQxRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c3b32b2a634b:0xed36eb56e71da4a4"}, {"name": "places/ChIJS2MqK7PDwoARpKQd51brNu0/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xZM1dXaElkMlZUYlRjM2VFYzBiRzl2T1ZGdWIyYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "6 months ago", "rating": 4, "text": {"text": "Had no idea this spot was such a big deal until our son introduced us to it! It’s definitely popular with the younger crowd, there was a pretty long line when we got there, but the vibe is fun.\n\nThey have a huge menu with so many flavored coffee options and different matcha offerings. We decided to try the Banana Cream Matcha and the Strawberry Cream Matcha. Both were delicious, though heads up, they are very sweet!\n\nIt’s a really nice place to grab a drink and hang out after church. For parking, there is a lot in the back, otherwise, you can usually find street parking right on Green Street.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Had no idea this spot was such a big deal until our son introduced us to it! It’s definitely popular with the younger crowd, there was a pretty long line when we got there, but the vibe is fun.\n\nThey have a huge menu with so many flavored coffee options and different matcha offerings. We decided to try the Banana Cream Matcha and the Strawberry Cream Matcha. Both were delicious, though heads up, they are very sweet!\n\nIt’s a really nice place to grab a drink and hang out after church. For parking, there is a lot in the back, otherwise, you can usually find street parking right on Green Street.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "regis kwong", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111212127579957762328/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUl8HquiHw9l5QMQ5U7ZfHcwVlgDIGHJeKbXiJ8K0pzF75VSytlaA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba8"}, "publishTime": "2025-12-28T22:06:46.379638235Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xZM1dXaElkMlZUYlRjM2VFYzBiRzl2T1ZGdWIyYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xZM1dXaElkMlZUYlRjM2VFYzBiRzl2T1ZGdWIyYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c3b32b2a634b:0xed36eb56e71da4a4"}, {"name": "places/ChIJS2MqK7PDwoARpKQd51brNu0/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21SNWNEa3pWVXQxYVZKM01qUjVjek5xYjBScGVsRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "rating": 4, "text": {"text": "Stopped by on a Saturday morning and the place was pretty busy, which is always a good sign. Luckily, seating is pretty abundant so it didn’t feel too cramped even with the crowd. There’s also parking in the back which made getting in and out pretty easy.\n\nTried a few drinks while I was there:\n\nBanana Cream Latte – Loved the nutty, sweet combo here. It wasn’t overly sweet, which I appreciated. The banana flavor was definitely more prominent while the coffee notes stayed a bit more in the background.\n\nCoffee Rain – The coffee flavor was a lot stronger in this one. The slight sweetness helped bring everything together and balance the drink nicely.\n\nMatcha Latte – I don’t drink matcha very often so I don’t have too much to compare it to, but it was smooth and easy to drink.\n\nThey also carry pastries and desserts from a local bakery, which is a nice touch if you’re looking for something small to go with your drink.\n\nOverall a solid coffee spot, especially if you’re meeting friends or looking for a place to hang out for a bit.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Stopped by on a Saturday morning and the place was pretty busy, which is always a good sign. Luckily, seating is pretty abundant so it didn’t feel too cramped even with the crowd. There’s also parking in the back which made getting in and out pretty easy.\n\nTried a few drinks while I was there:\n\nBanana Cream Latte – Loved the nutty, sweet combo here. It wasn’t overly sweet, which I appreciated. The banana flavor was definitely more prominent while the coffee notes stayed a bit more in the background.\n\nCoffee Rain – The coffee flavor was a lot stronger in this one. The slight sweetness helped bring everything together and balance the drink nicely.\n\nMatcha Latte – I don’t drink matcha very often so I don’t have too much to compare it to, but it was smooth and easy to drink.\n\nThey also carry pastries and desserts from a local bakery, which is a nice touch if you’re looking for something small to go with your drink.\n\nOverall a solid coffee spot, especially if you’re meeting friends or looking for a place to hang out for a bit.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Macato", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110766689694632157173/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOPEkQz22TNjdwTqdi2EaWqPnxURIbSixfVYhlimH2A1DJjUY=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2"}, "publishTime": "2026-03-10T21:08:17.577377930Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21SNWNEa3pWVXQxYVZKM01qUjVjek5xYjBScGVsRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21SNWNEa3pWVXQxYVZKM01qUjVjek5xYjBScGVsRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c3b32b2a634b:0xed36eb56e71da4a4"}, {"name": "places/ChIJS2MqK7PDwoARpKQd51brNu0/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21KSVdVc3labWRMYWtGUWFHMDNYM1JaWW5wRGVsRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a week ago", "rating": 4, "text": {"text": "I waver between giving this cafe a 4 or 5 stars. I got the matcha latte and it was quite good - the flavor is strong albeit tempered by the pronounced taste of the oat milk. The WiFi didn’t work and it was quite busy with very strong AC.", "languageCode": "en"}, "ori